  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic movies?",
  "response": "There are many romantic movies that have captured audiences' hearts over the years. Here are some of the most recognized and beloved romantic films, spanning various styles and eras:\n\n1. **The Notebook (2004)** - A classic love story based on Nicholas Sparks' novel about a summer romance that endures over several years.\n2. **Pride and Prejudice (2005)** - An adaptation of Jane Austen's novel, focusing on the complicated relationship between Elizabeth Bennet and Mr. Darcy.\n3. **Titanic (1997)** - A tragic love story set against the backdrop of the ill-fated ocean liner.\n4. **Casablanca (1942)** - A timeless tale of love and sacrifice during World War II.\n5. **La La Land (2016)** - A modern musical that explores the romance and challenges between an aspiring actress and a jazz musician in Los Angeles.\n6. **When Harry Met Sally... (1989)** - A romantic comedy exploring the question of whether men and women can truly be friends.\n7. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004)** - A unique take on love and memory, exploring the emotional complexity of relationships.\n8. **Notting Hill (1999)** - A charming romantic comedy about an ordinary man who falls in love with a famous actress.\n9. **A Walk to Remember (2002)** - Another adaptation of a Nicholas Sparks novel, focusing on the transformative power of love.\n10. **Before Sunrise (1995)** - The first in a trilogy, this film follows a spontaneous connection between two travelers in Vienna.\n\nThese films are widely celebrated for their storytelling, performances, and emotional impact, making them enduring favorites in the romance genre.",
